\\Executive-Level Findings
"I analyzed retail sales data containing nearly 10,000 records using MySQL. The company generated $2.3M in sales and $286K in profit. Technology was the highest-performing category with a 17.4% profit margin, while Furniture generated strong revenue but only a 2.49% margin. Further analysis showed Furniture had the highest average discount rate, suggesting discounting negatively impacted profitability. Regional analysis identified the West region as the strongest contributor to both sales and profit."